course.subject: HUMA
course.name: East Asia and the West: Cultures in Contact
course.description: This course is an overview of the history of cultural, diplomatic, and economic relations between East Asia and the West from the 19th to the 20th century, with emphasis on China and Japan and their search for modernity. It examines not only the actual contacts between Westerners and the peoples in East Asia but also their changing perceptions of each other and of themselves through time.
